{SOUTH cannot rebid the 5-card \S suit, cannot support NORTH's \Ds, 
and cannot bid Notrump without a \H stopper.

So she bids 3\C, New Minor Forcing, asking NORTH to describe his hand further.

NORTH doesn't have three \Ss, nor does he have four \Hs. 
But he does have \Hs stopped, so bids 2NT. South is not strong 
enough to bid game so she passes.}

